// ============================================================================
// LOAD BALANCE ESTIMATES
// ============================================================================
//
// Mesh: 400(x) × 486(y) × 25(z) = 4,860,000 cells
//
// 64 cores:   76k cells/core  (good for testing)
// 128 cores:  38k cells/core  (RECOMMENDED)
// 256 cores:  19k cells/core  (great for production)
//
// Memory per core (rough):
// - Mesh + fields: ~2-3 GB/core at 128 cores
// - Total: ~256-384 GB for 128 cores
//
// Scaling:
// - Strong scaling should be good up to ~20k cells/core
// - Beyond 256 cores, returns diminish for this mesh
//
// Communication:
// - Mainly in X and Z directions
// - Each X-face: 486×6 = ~3k cells → reasonable
// - Each Z-face: 13×486 = ~6k cells → fine

// ============================================================================
// RUNNING ON POLIMI CLUSTER
// ============================================================================
//
// Typical workflow:
//
// 1. Decompose:
//    decomposePar -force
//
// 2. Check balance:
//    ls -d processor* | wc -l    # Should match numberOfSubdomains
//
// 3. Run (SLURM example):
//    #!/bin/bash
//    #SBATCH --nodes=4
//    #SBATCH --ntasks-per-node=32
//    #SBATCH --time=48:00:00
//    #SBATCH --mem=384G
//
//    mpirun -np 128 compInterFoam -parallel | tee log.compInterFoam
//
// 4. Reconstruct:
//    reconstructPar -latestTime
//    # or
//    reconstructPar -time "0.1,0.5,1,5,10"

